# ===============================================
# SIMPLIFIED GIT IGNORE FOR MICROSERVICES ARCHITECTURE
# ===============================================

# 1. GENERAL FILES AND PYTHON CACHES
# These files are often generated by the IDE or local execution.
# They apply to the Capstone, Songs, and Pictures directories.
# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*/__pycache__/
*.py[co]
.coverage
.cache/
.pytest_cache/

# 2. ENVIRONMENTS AND DEPENDENCIES
# Local virtual environments are not versioned.
# Although Docker manages them, these folders may be created during local development.
.env
.venv
env/
venv/
lib/
lib64/
.mypy_cache/

# 3. APPLICATION SPECIFIC FILES (Django / Flask)

# Capstone (Django)
# The database must be ignored even if it's in a volume,
# because the host file can be created locally.
# The -journal file is the SQLite transaction operation.
db.sqlite3
db.sqlite3-journal
*.log

# Songs and Pictures (Flask)
# Flask instance/cache files
instance/
.webassets-cache

# 4. TOOLS AND SYSTEM FILES
# Development tool files (VS, VS Code, Spyder, etc.)
.idea/
.vs/
.vscode/
.spyderproject
.spyproject
*.manifest
*.spec

# 5. OPERATING SYSTEM FILES
# macOS / Windows / Linux files (add as needed)
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
